The paper deals with protocols for interactive communication, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the tolerance of these protocols to adversarial noise, which is a topic that falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper deals with the adaptivity of protocols, which is a topic that falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
